<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trias-Blasi &amp; G. Parmar" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Causonis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Causonis sessilifolia" order="Vitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Causonis sessilifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Causonis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Causonis japonica" order="Vitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Causonis japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Thunb. ex Murray) Raf. share similarity in possessing 5-foliolate leaves, but the former taxon has sessile leaves and 2-5-furcate tendrils (vs. petiolate leaves and 2-3-furcate tendrils in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. japonica" order="Vitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">C. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
